--- title: "CAMH sid issue" date: 2023-03-05 author: Santiago Sotelo --- ::: {.cell} ::: ## Problem - In communication with Alexander Daros from CAMH Institute, it is informed that there is a problem with `sid` code of some users that are been defaulted to `null`. - We have to take into consideration that sid's should not have the company prefix, for example, instead of camh_0001 should be 0001. ## Objectives 1. Identify the CAMH observation with sid defaulted to `null` and other problems in `sid` variable. For the purpose of this report, we are going to use the data from BecharaReport API gathered in 2023-03-04. This data has 1'780'739 observations and 80 variables, and can be found in the following Dropbox path: Mobio Interactive Dropbox/Research/RWD/Shared R Scripts/Input csv/BecharaReportFull-2023-03-04T05_15_17.csv After applying the procedure to reduce the number of duplicates in the data, we have 71'897 observations in data.
